parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking and leaking of the fuel tank can cause fuel vapors to escape, leading to a potential fire hazard, and may also cause the motorcycle to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Fuel tank develops hairline cracks or stress fractures
particularly at the right front mounting tab; fuel vapors or liquid fuel leak from the tank; fuel seepage apparent; fuel tank weld cracks and starts leaking fuel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or lack of response from the manufacturer and dealerships in addressing the fuel tank recall can leave motorcycle owners without a safe mode of transportation for an extended period, causing inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Long wait times for repairs; lack of communication from the manufacturer and dealerships; no estimated time of repair (ETA) provided; owners are left without a safe motorcycle for an extended period.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission gear shifting issues can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission pops out of gear
the transmission will not downshift to first gear without lifting the shifter
the transmission downshifts on its own
and the clutch does not disengage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hydraulic clutch malfunction can cause the gears to become stuck and the clutch to not disengage, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch malfunctions when the bike becomes hot
and the clutch does not disengage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stator and rectifier can cause the vehicle to lose power while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power while driving
